{"data":{"post":{"id":"39ca81e0-4a4c-5de7-a41b-305dc52920b0","html":"<p><a href=\"http://www.artrustee.com/\" title=\"Artrustee\">Artrustee</a>, an art consultancy company based in <strong>Tel Aviv</strong>, has invited me to review an exhibit of Israeli Art at the <a href=\"http://www.thegallerysoho.com/\" title=\"The Gallery Soho\">Gallery Soho</a> last week. <strong>With more than 17 of the most prominent artists from Tel Aviv, the four-day exhibit confirms how exciting Tel Aviv’s contemporary art scene is fast becoming</strong>. In Freedom of Expression: True Colours, the artists explore themes of identity, territory and sexual liberation with a particular focus on gay and lesbian issues.</p>\n<p>Some of the artists that participated in the exhibit were: <strong><a href=\"http://www.ionone.com/pntperez.htm\">Raphael “Rafi” Perez</a>, Dan Reisner,Ronit Yanizki, Ammon David Ar, Sichi Gilad, Uri Gershuni, Maya Kapelushnik,<a href=\"http://www.howardfox.com/\" title=\"Howard Fox\"> Howard Fox</a></strong> and so much more. Please read the article <a href=\"http://www.artrustee.com/freedom-of-expression-true-colours?view=article&#x26;article=202\" title=\"Freedom of Expression\">here</a> and tell me what you think =)</p>\n<p>\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/danreisner_sculptures_lrg3ow-3d515cfb4310f44ca3cd267fda2ca1b9-55fd7.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; null; max-width: 640px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        